According to the Commission, uneven blooms are reported in the areas around the major municipalities of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier.
The algal bloom extends along more than 20 miles of the coast, from northern Pinellas to southern Lee.
Spots can be seen about a mile and a half out in the sea outside Hillsborough, but in fewer places than last week.
Algae blooming has also been observed in the municipality of Pasco.
Mean high concentrations in or off the coast of Pinellas have been reported during the past week. Outside of the Hillsborough coast low to high concentrations, background concentrations to high concentrations in Manatee, background concentrations to high concentrations in or off the coast of Sarasota.
Reports of respiratory irritation continue to come from the major municipalities of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
There were no reports of respiratory irritation in northwestern Florida last week.
